column5: Not even sure if the title makes any sense..  Out a couple of weeks ago targeting Smallies. Water temp was still 59 degrees, leaves were turning colours Smallies were attacking Crawfish...Yum 3 inch craw          Same fish    Was trying to get the colours in the pic
Sick! Beautiful time of year and great fish!  Way to go man(I recognize that spot, be there $2000 and 20 hours later)  ???  Baits/depths/COLOURS?
Jigging with a green pumpkin coloured crawfish in 25 F O W   Ok, I'll wait for ya Bro
Nice looking report. You guys sure do well in the fall on those crawbugs. Beauty smalljaws.
